{
  "name": "kastner-jrl-trends-1999-pk-responses-f4c5a4",
  "title": "JRL 1999 Trends List with Peter Kastner Responses",
  "description": "Internal Aberdeen-era memo: a list of 9 trends for 1999 compiled by 'JRL' (John R. Logan, Aberdeen Group co-founder, partner, and board chairman) followed by detailed 'PK Response' annotations from Peter Kastner. Trends covered: application integration, Y2K remediation, Y2K contingency planning at the business-unit level, Intel banner year, #1-vendor market-share gains, telecom switching, Sun's enterprise data center ascendancy, Windows 2000 slow adoption, post-Y2K e-commerce. Kastner adds three extension trends: who owns security, the year of the object, and computing as a utility / ISP business. Primary-source artifact of Kastner thinking in 1999.",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "created": "2026-04-24",
